7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1288, L.D. 1927, “An Act to Protect
10 Housing Quality by Enacting Mold Inspection, Notification and Remediation
11 Requirements”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Add Mold to the Implied Warranty and Covenant of Habitability'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 14 MRSA §6021, sub-§1, as enacted by PL 1977, c. 401, §4, is repealed
17 and the following enacted in its place:
18 1. Definition. As used in this section, unless the context otherwise indicates, the
19 following terms have the following meanings.
20 A. "Dwelling unit" includes mobile homes, apartments, buildings and other structures,
21 including the common areas thereof, that are rented for human habitation.
22 B. "Leaking event" means a water leak from flooding or a system or structural failure,
23 such as a failure of a roof, window, door, plumbing system, foundation or appliance.
24 Sec. 2. 14 MRSA §6021, sub-§6-B is enacted to read:
25 6-B. Mold; bacteria; other biological organisms. It is a breach of the implied
26 warranty of fitness for human habitation when a landlord offers for rent a dwelling unit in
27 which there is a leaking event, chronic moisture or humidity conditions outside of the
28 control of a tenant that result in the growth of mold, bacteria or other biological organisms.
29 A municipality may adopt more stringent standards by ordinance than those provided in
30 this section.'
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
