COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1288, L.D. 1927
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment provides that
33 when a landlord offers for rent a dwelling unit and that landlord knows or should know that
44 the dwelling unit has mold, bacteria or other biological organisms that are injurious to the
55 health of occupants, then it is a breach of the implied warranty and covenant of habitability.
66 The amendment also allows municipalities to adopt more stringent standards related to the
77 implied warranty and covenant of habitability.
88 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
99 (See attached)
